Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) uses solid oxide as an electrolyte and has a high-power generation efficiency.
Titulo: Characterization of Ca-doped YCoO3 Perovskite-type oxide as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: One of the major problems in the development of SOFC is the side reaction that occurs at the interface between the electrode and the electrolyte.
Titulo: Characterization of Ca-doped YCoO3 Perovskite-type oxide as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: (Y, Ca)CoO3-delta(3) materials were evaluated as a new air electrode material to replace the conventional (La, Sr)CoO3 materials.
Titulo: Characterization of Ca-doped YCoO3 Perovskite-type oxide as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Y0.8Ca0.1CoO3-delta has good compatibility with Y-stabilized ZrO2 (YSZ) electrolyte.
Titulo: Characterization of Ca-doped YCoO3 Perovskite-type oxide as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, the power generation performance was equal to or better than the conventional SOFC cells.
Titulo: Characterization of Ca-doped YCoO3 Perovskite-type oxide as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
